## 2. Changes Summary

### Frontend Refactoring
- Split monolithic index.html (1361 lines) into:
  - index.html (40 lines): pure markup, external refs
  - style.css (474 lines): all styles
  - app.js (844 lines): all JavaScript logic
- Benefits: easier maintenance, independent editing, better caching

### Prompt Management
- Migrated system prompt from inline Scala string + host.md
  -> src/main/resources/prompts/system.md
- repl.scala: loadSystemPrompt() reads from /prompts/system.md
- Old host.md removed

### Static File Serving
- WebSocketRoutes.scala: added /style.css and /app.js route handlers
- Whitelist-based serving (only style.css, app.js allowed)

### UI Bug Fixes (v1.00.017)
- Thinking placeholder bubble now disappears on text/tool start
- Tool history save/restore cycle fixed (no more duplicate tool cards)

## 3. Code Review Findings

### Critical: None

### Moderate:
1. WebFetchTool.scala:60-61 - cache expiry check uses > instead of >=
   Status: Minor, cache may serve expired entry by 1ms. Acceptable.

2. shell.scala:23-25 - PersistentShell uses thread pools without shutdown hooks
   Status: Process-level lifecycle. kill() shuts them down. Acceptable.

3. WebSocketRoutes.scala: static file whitelist is hardcoded
   Status: Intentional security measure. Acceptable.

### Minor:
1. app.js contains large inline Lottie JSON (spinnerJson, toolSpinnerJson)
   Status: Could be externalized, but keeps app self-contained offline.

2. style.css single file is still large (474 lines)
   Status: Could further split by component, but current separation is sufficient.

## 4. Security Check
- Static file serving uses whitelist (style.css, app.js only)
- No path traversal possible (http4s StaticFile handles this)
- Prompt file is classpath resource, not web-accessible

## 5. Conclusion
ALL CHECKS PASSED. Code is ready for merge.

